com.camerontec.catalys.server.test

Class CatalysJMXConfigurationClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.test.CatalysJMXConfigurationClient

  • public class CatalysJMXConfigurationClient
extends Object
    Utility class encapsulating some common tasks for configuring Catalys remotely via the JMX configuration API. This class is shared by all the SampleJMXConfigurationClient* classes in this package.

    Note that this code has no dependency on the Catalys libraries.

    Note also that this class is only a template and does not cover all of the JMX configuration API. See Configuration_via_JMX.html for a comprehensive list of all JMX configuration operations and attributes.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CatalysJMXConfigurationClient

        public CatalysJMXConfigurationClient(int mBeanServerPort,
                                     String applicationID,
                                     boolean verbose,
                                     boolean connectThroughManagementAgent)
                              throws MalformedURLException,
                                     IOException
        Creates an instance and connects to the MBean (Catalys/LM/MA) server listening on port 'mBeanServerPort'.
        Parameters:
        mBeanServerPort - The port on which the MBean server is listening for JMX connections.
        applicationID - The applicationID of the server we want to configure
        verbose - If true, the client will log all JMX operations as they happen
        connectThroughManagementAgent - whether to connect to the Catalys Server directly (false) or via the Management Agent (true). This parameter determines the structure of the MBean names.
        Throws:
        MalformedURLException - incorrect URL used to connect to the MBean server
        IOException - if the connection to the MBean server cannot be made because of a communication problem
